        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 12:45AM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 1243 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from City Island to Elmont. Movement was northeast
at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Jamaica, Valley Stream, Huntington Station, Glen Cove, Garden City,
Syosset, Mineola, Huntington, Westbury, Great Neck, Northport, Oyster
Bay, Bayside, Elmont, and Whitestone.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
